			<description><![CDATA[<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Are you a designer who loves building both beautiful and useful products? Do you have the ability to talk about theoretical concepts in typography but also understand what it takes to build and ship products during the day-to-day? Are you looking to make a lasting impact in a budding social media NYC start-up looking to shape the future of digital marketing? The Adaptly team is looking for a UI/UX Lead to help elevate our industry-leading social advertising solution and overall corporate brand to the next level.</p>
<p>
<strong>Day-to-day Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
- Define and execute Adaptly&rsquo;s overall UI/UX vision<br />
- Create design deliverables including high and low-fidelity sketches and layouts<br />
- Actively consider user interaction with respect to created design deliverables<br />
- Craft clear, creative and compelling marketing collateral and assets in different mediums<br />
- Design and conduct user research using both quantitative and qualitative methods<br />
- Collaborate with key stakeholders to carry-out product development and product marketing initiatives with an emphasis on driving towards key business outcomes<br />
- Provide expertise and guidance to Adaptly&rsquo;s current UI/UX and product development teams<br />
- Take on product management and support responsibilities as needed including:<br />
- Collect user and client feedback to formulate user stories for development<br />
- Engaging internal and external users understand and resolve product issues</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualities of the Ideal Candidate</strong></p>
<p>
- The ability to communicate in a concise and precise manner is an absolute must<br />
- A collaborative approach in working with the diverse, idiosyncratic team at Adaptly<br />
- Can and willing to tackle challenges from the left and right side of the brain<br />
- An attitude that no task is either too big or small<br />
- Possessing an obsessive level of self-awareness to continuously improve<br />
- Passion to always stay ahead and hunger that is never relinquished</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
- A four-year university degree in relevant field is preferred &ndash; BFA/MFA a plus<br />
- Relevant technical design experience (e.g., Illustrator, Omnigraffle)<br />
- Prior experience in an enterprise B2B tech company start-up a plus<br />
- Familiarity with relevant front-end development technologies (e.g., Javascript)<br />
- Experience working within the Agile methodology is preferred<br />
- Previous experience directly managing UI/UX professionals is preferred<br />
- A unique skill or passion of some form (music, sports, curling, farming, etc.)</p>
