			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Do you enjoy tackling challenging strategic business problems while resolving the day-to-day nitty-gritty product details? Can you speak the language of both enterprise sales executives and senior software architects? Do you have the intuition and passion for design and truly great software? And are you looking to make a lasting impact in a budding social media NYC start-up? The Adaptly team is looking for an experienced product manager to help us take on the growing challenge and opportunities in the constantly evolving social media environment. You&rsquo;ll be immediately tasked to independently learn and then tackle a variety of challenges that are new and unexplored. You&rsquo;ll be working with an extremely talented and diverse group of individuals that will challenge, frustrate, inspire and collaborate with you at every turn of our journey. You&rsquo;ll be asked to bring 100% of your intelligence, wit, talent and patience each and every single day. And you&rsquo;ll love it.</p>
<p>
Day-to-day Responsibilities</p>
<p>
- Execute industry / market research to drive product development and innovation<br />
- Gather appropriate user and buyer product and feature requirements<br />
- Define and present strategic product priorities, roadmaps and timelines<br />
- Engage product marketing function to align product with market message / position<br />
- Make strategic and spontaneous product decisions with respect to product scope<br />
- Collaborate and lead internal stakeholders towards product / feature alignment<br />
- Work with design and development teams to successfully deliver working software<br />
- Manage the day-to-day relationships with key distribution and supply-side partners<br />
- Assist internal and external users understand and resolve product defects and issues</p>
<p>
Qualities of the Ideal Candidate:</p>
<p>
- The ability to communicate in a concise and precise manner is an absolute must<br />
- A collaborative approach in working with the diverse, idiosyncratic team at Adaptly<br />
- Can and willing to tackle challenges from the left and right side of the brain<br />
- An attitude that no task is either too big or small &ndash; and doing it with a smile<br />
- Possessing an obsessive level of self-awareness to continuously improve<br />
- Passion to always stay ahead &amp; hunger that is never relinquished</p>
<p>
Qualifications:</p>
<p>
- A four-year university degree is preferred &ndash; MBA a plus<br />
- 5-7 years of product management experience is preferred (3-5 for MBA graduates)<br />
- Prior product management experience in an enterprise B2B Tech Startup is required - relevant skills include:<br />
- Attaining appropriate research and requirements for given product or feature<br />
- Creating and presenting product vision, roadmaps and timeframes<br />
- Managing a prioritized product backlog with requisite prioritization<br />
- Improvisational ability to generate creative solutions to tough trade-off decisions<br />
- Follow-through on the entire product development / management lifecycle<br />
- Prior experience working in an Agile development environment in is required - relevant skills include:<br />
- Ability to facilitate estimation, prioritization and assignment team sessions<br />
- Knowledge to make key business judgments with respect to product scope<br />
- Prior experience working with appropriate tool-sets (JIRA, Trello, Excel, etc.)<br />
- Intuition to effectively communicate relevant development and design topics<br />
- Prior program-management experience in an enterprise B2B Tech startup is preferred<br />
- Prior product marketing experience in an enterprise B2B Tech startup is preferred<br />
- Technical competency in Excel, PowerPoint is a must &ndash; SQL knowledge preferred<br />
- A unique skill or passion of some form (music, sports, curling, farming, etc.)</p>
